0. Example is borrowed from: https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go/tree/master/examples/leader-election
1. Need to modify the go.mod under main directory
2. Change based on https://screenshot.googleplex.com/0hiDpo30aVT
3. Then run tidy/vendor, according to vendor faq: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/P4LZnkGSOi2
4. Then run the file under watt/ directory, with 
    $ go run *.go -id=1 -kubeconfig=$HOME/.kube/config
    $ go run *.go -id=2 -kubeconfig=$HOME/.kube/config
    $ go run *.go -id=3 -kubeconfig=$HOME/.kube/config
   in different terminals, and it should work.

